}], "Picture",
 CellID->297041312,ExpressionUUID->"fb8dddee-616a-46fe-8ba6-70deecfe06e9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 3",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". An implementation of the Toffoli gate based on the conditional-unitary \
gate with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"V", "=", 
    SqrtBox["X"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "48ec9736-3696-4f50-a27b-89410a5df8e3"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteCaption",
 CellID->444082079,ExpressionUUID->"d4909f99-7afc-4edd-b174-d02f08c27f36"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Therefore, putting ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"V", "=", 
    SqrtBox["X"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e32b4654-6c05-4aaf-befb-ea385cb87c57"],
 ", the quantum circuit on the left-hand side reproduces the Toffoli gate. \
Here we have chosen a combination in the particular order, but any \
combination of arbitrary order of the three components gives the same result; \
see the following demonstration."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->318325295,ExpressionUUID->"23b0cc22-ac07-4485-a1ee-90dd8e2ebb08"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Demonstration", "Subsection",
 CellID->1817234603,ExpressionUUID->"d9425ecd-a522-4fdd-a150-b93126ef643c"],

Cell["\<\
For demonstration, here we examine several slightly different implements of \
the Toffoli gate. First, recall the quantum circuit model of the Toffoli gate.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1169838411,ExpressionUUID->"4909c8bc-563e-4904-bfed-bafeaf8231ba"],

