    "history" -> {"13", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"CNOT", "controlled-unitary gates"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Tech Note", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "The multi - control NOT gate is similar to the CNOT gate on two qubits, \
but it is controlled by a register of multiple qubits rather than by a single \
qubit . Let TemplateBox[{c}, \
Ket]\\[Congruent]TemplateBox[{RowBox[{SubscriptBox[c, 1], SubscriptBox[c, 2], \
SubscriptBox[\\[CenterEllipsis]c, n]}]}, Ket] and TemplateBox[{t}, Ket] be \
the computational basis states of the control register and the target qubit, \
respectively . Under the multi-control NOT gate, they transform as \
TemplateBox[{c}, Ket]\\[CircleTimes]TemplateBox[{t}, \
Ket]\\[RightTeeArrow]TemplateBox[{c}, \
Ket]\\[CircleTimes]TemplateBox[{RowBox[{RowBox[{(, RowBox[{SubscriptBox[c, \
1], SubscriptBox[c, 2], SubscriptBox[\\[CenterEllipsis]c, n]}], )}], \
\\[CirclePlus], t}]}, Ket] or equivalently,", "synonyms" -> {}, 
    "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "Multi-Control NOT Gate", "titlemodifier" -> 
    "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> "Multi-Control NOT Gate", 
    "type" -> "Tech Note", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MultiControlNOTGate"}},
